main event: A sighting of a rectangular object, tapering to a point, was reported in Gulkana, Alaska on 19 Mar 1961.
interesting points: The object was observed traveling at a high rate of speed for 10 seconds., It changed color from bright white to burning yellow., The size of the object was comparable to a baseball., There were no visible means of propulsion observed., It was suggested that the sighting could have been a meteor or missile, but it was classified as not positively identified.
sighted object: rectangular object tapering to a point
